    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>All Python examples on this page use finite dicts as probability distributions. The paper works over arbitrary measurable spaces, continuous distributions, and the full subdistribution monad on StdBorel. The composition laws are the same; the generality is not. Every example is tagged <strong class="text-green-400">Simplified</strong> unless marked otherwise — the structure is preserved, the measure theory is dropped.</p>
    <p>The bridge theorem section is tagged <strong class="text-green-400">Exact</strong> — the Python computes the same equivalence the Lean proof verifies.</p>

